    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for pki-core.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 9.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The Public Key Infrastructure (PKI) Core contains fundamental packages required by Rocky Enterprise Software Foundation Certificate System.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* pki-core: access to external entities when parsing XML can lead to XXE (CVE-2022-2414)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
